he Risk Management Officer performs a supporting role in underwriting, measuring, monitoring and analysing corporate/consumer credit risks.

  Designing and implementing an overall risk management process for the organisation, which includes an analysis of the financial impact on the company when risks occur
  Performing a risk assessment: Analysing current risks and identifying potential risks that are affecting the company
  Relate macro-economic concepts to credit risk management and be able to source and interpret relevant macro-economic information to support effective risk analysis, management and mitigation.
  Understand the credit products, approval process, risk documentation to facilitate credit administration, limit management and credit monitoring as well as consumer lending aspects.
  Performing a risk evaluation: Evaluating the company’s previous handling of risks, and comparing potential risks with criteria set out by the company such as costs and legal requirements
  Building risk awareness amongst staff by providing support and training within the company
